Hon. Prime Minister, what I am trying to say is that a retirement is different to a resignation. I am telling you with responsibility. I will present this case with responsibility. That is why we want time. We do not want to get involved personally with the Hon. Prime Minister on any matter. He has tried his best, perhaps in a way to resolve it, but the Bar Association came and forced him to accept their conditions. - [Interruption.] You said that the Bar Association forced the Government to accept these conditions of forcibly removing Mohan Peiris. What you said is recorded. You said it just two hours ago. What you said is true. That is what happened. You were trying to resolve, but the Bar Association took the matter into their hands and forced you all to act like thugs and throw out Chief Justice, Mohan Peiris and install a lady in that chair. That is the fact.
